Closed String Tachyon Condensation 
The issue we wish to address, in its most prototypical
form and in the notation of, is the propagation of
superstrings on manifolds that could be locally modeled as singular
algebraic varieties of the orbifold type (cf.  for
some review on this subject). In otherwords, the background
geometry of concern is
^d-1,1  ^10-d /where  is an orbifold group, embedded in some Lie
isometry group of (subspaces of) the  factor. The algebraic
structure of  determines the physics of the transverse
