phenomenological importance.

Attention has been paid, until over the last few years, to  
which give rise to supersymmetric gauge theories, the R-symmetries 
of which are then interpreted as the abovementioned isometry groups. 
Indeed, when  is a discrete finite subgroup of special
unitary groups, in particular , the Gorenstein condition
(cf. e.g. ) assures us that the resolution of the
orbifold gives a smooth
Calabi-Yau manifold (q.v.  for ,
