of , i.e., conjugacy classes of the
discrete finite small subgroups of , together with
their quivers for the minimal resolution in the sense of
f:genreso , each of which has a generalised
Hirzebruch-Jung continued fraction associated therewith.
We see that all these groups are very simple in that they afford the
direct product structure; the remarkable fact is that every orbifold of
 is isomorphic to a member of this simple list above.



A non-Abelian Example 
Armed with this list, let us discuss tachyon condensation associated
therewith.
