(Hilb ^n(^2))_
((^2)^n / S_n )_^2 /  .
This construction distinguished the Hilbert scheme as the (crepant)
minimal
resolution and provided an explicit mapping of the (non-trivial)
irreducible 
representations with the exceptional divisors.

Into the Hilbert scheme resolution we shall not delve too far. The key
point
for our purposes is the following theorem due to A. Ishii:
 
For small subgroups , 
the Ito-Nakamura construction for the
McKay Correspondence still holds if instead of considering
Irrep,
we consider a subset, the so-called special representations .
The definition of these representations is rather technical and
we briefly touch upon it. Let 
